## USER RESEARCH

### Top 5 Pain Points (from forums, Reddit, Quora)
1. **"It chipped before the celebration was over"** — gel in particular frustrates users who pay for a manicure and chip it within a week; the Mother's Day stakes make this anxiety worse
2. **"My nails were destroyed underneath"** — fear of nail damage from both acrylics (filing, acid primers) and gel (acetone dehydration from frequent removal every 2 weeks)
3. **"I don't know what to ask for at the salon"** — confusion between gel polish, hard gel, BIAB, builder gel, overlay; readers don't know the vocabulary
4. **"BIAB is too expensive / not available everywhere"** — frustration that BIAB is newer, harder to find, and costs more than a standard gel manicure
5. **"I wanted length but BIAB couldn't give me that"** — confusion about whether BIAB can extend length (it can for short-medium, but not dramatic stiletto/coffin lengths)

**User Sentiment:** Primarily confused and slightly anxious — they want to look good for one specific occasion without committing to months of maintenance or risking nail damage.

