## VOICE & TONE RECOMMENDATION

**Recommended Voice:** Knowledgeable friend who has had every type of manicure and works adjacent to the industry — not a brand, not a tech manual.

**Tone Characteristics:**
- Warm but direct — no hedging, no "it depends" without a follow-up answer
- Occasion-aware — this is about one special day, not a general lifestyle piece
- Demystifying — translate technical nail vocabulary into plain English throughout
- Confident — make a recommendation, don't leave the reader floating
- British English throughout — "colour," "favour," "mum," not "mom" in prose (though primary keyword uses "mother's" to match search intent)

**Language Style:** Use second person ("you," "your mum") directly. Introduce technical terms once with a plain-English gloss ("BIAB — that is, Builder in a Bottle"). Avoid "amazing," "stunning," "literally," "game-changer." No em dashes.

**Audience Match:** The reader is either a mum treating herself or an adult child helping Mum decide. She is practical, slightly time-pressured, and moderately beauty-literate — she knows what gel nails are but may have heard BIAB for the first time six months ago.

