## MDX COMPONENT SPEC — Interactive "Which Nail Is Right for Mum?" Quiz

This section is specific to the MDX/JSX environment and gives the writing agent everything needed to brief or build the component.

### Why This Component
Static pros/cons tables are what every competitor uses. An inline quiz turns a passive scan into a decision. Completion rates for embedded quizzes are significantly higher than static content. The quiz resolves the primary user pain point (confusion about which system to choose) in a personalised, low-friction way. It also increases time-on-page.

### Component Behaviour
- 3 questions, multiple choice, single select per question
- Results display inline immediately after Q3 (no page reload)
- 3 possible results: Gel Polish, BIAB, or Acrylic
- Result card includes: system name, one-line verdict, durability window, who it is for
- No email gate, no external API — fully client-side state with `useState`

### Questions and Logic

**Q1 — How long do you need the nails to last?**
- A: "Just through Mother's Day weekend" → Gel
- B: "Two to three weeks without worrying" → BIAB
- C: "As long as humanly possible" → Acrylic

**Q2 — What matters most to you?**
- A: "Speed and affordability" → Gel
- B: "Nail health and natural growth" → BIAB
- C: "Maximum length and structure" → Acrylic

**Q3 — How would you describe your nails?**
- A: "Naturally strong, I just want colour" → Gel
- B: "Weak, thin, or prone to breaking" → BIAB
- C: "I want dramatic length — mine won't grow" → Acrylic

**Scoring Logic (majority vote of 3 answers):**
- 2+ Gel answers → Result: Gel Polish
- 2+ BIAB answers → Result: BIAB
- 2+ Acrylic answers → Result: Acrylic
- Tie (1 each of two types) → Default to BIAB (positioned as the balanced middle-ground)

### Result Card Copy (for each outcome)

**Gel Polish**
> Best for: Mums who want a quick, glossy update without commitment.
> Lasts: 10–14 days. Chip-resistant, soak-off removal, wide colour range.
> Book: A standard gel manicure, 45–60 minutes.

**BIAB (Builder in a Bottle)**
> Best for: Mums who want their natural nails to come out stronger than they went in.
> Lasts: 3–4 weeks with infills. Protective overlay, flexible, nail-healthy removal.
> Book: A BIAB appointment, allow 60–90 minutes.

**Acrylic**
> Best for: Mums who want length, structure, and a manicure that survives anything.
> Lasts: 3–4 weeks+ with fills. Most rigid, most durable, widest shape options.
> Book: A full set with your nail technician — ask about infills at 2–3 weeks.

### Component Placement in Post
Place after H2 #7 ("Which One Is Right for Mum?"). Introduce it with a short prose paragraph, then drop the component, then follow with the editorial verdict section. The quiz should not be the final word — the written section after it adds nuance and internal links.

